title: IGNITE-3897 Test transactional behaviour of caches during rolling restart
body:
This submission includes 2 new tests for the IgniteCacheFailoverTestSuite that validate the results of an aggregation function running against a cluster undergoing rolling restart.

It also includes a new Assertion, EventualAssertion - this assertion has a timeout and retests the assertion with exponential back-off until successful, or failure, allowing tests to wait in a deterministic fashion for a condition before continuing with the test. This is particularly useful in Rolling-Restart type tests, to ensure after a node is killed that the system has time to rebalance before continuing with the restarts.
